First Lady Melania Trump convened the Interagency Working Group on Youth Programs at the White House to discuss programs that align with her Be Best initiative. The meeting focused on the well-being of children, social media safety, and families affected by opioid abuse. Various agency representatives, including Secretary DeVos of the Department of Education and Secretary Carson of the Department of Housing and Urban Development, shared information about programs that positively impact children's lives. Some of the programs discussed included the Department of Housing and Urban Development's Strong Families Initiative, the Department of Health and Human Services' neonatal opioid withdrawal syndrome treatment program, and the Federal Emergency Management Agency's efforts to prepare children for emergencies. The First Lady expressed her commitment to working with the Interagency Working Group to provide children with the necessary tools and support for success.